---
layout: base
permalink: /record/
title: "The Record"
description: "The Record — three founding documents anchor the work of E5 Enclave: Parallel Negros, Measure the Wound, Restitution 246. Published openly, audited against practice, built to be cited."
breadcrumbs:
  - { label: "The Record" }
---
<header class="vc-page-head reveal">
  <div class="vc-page-eyebrow">— The Record —</div>
  <h1 class="vc-page-h">Dispatches from <em>the Coalition.</em></h1>
  <p class="vc-page-deck">Three documents anchor the founding work — a Think Tank dispatch, the foundational record of the harms we repair, and the campaign framework for restitution. Each is published openly, audited against practice, and built to be cited.</p>
</header>

<section class="vc-record" style="background: var(--vc-bone); padding-top:24px;">
  <div class="vc-record-grid reveal">
    {% for paper in collections.paper %}
    <article class="vc-record-card{% if paper.data.order == 1 %} vc-record-lead{% endif %}">
      <div class="kind">{{ paper.data.kind }}</div>
      <h2 class="title">{{ paper.data.title }}</h2>
      <p class="lede">{{ paper.data.deck or paper.data.description }}</p>
      <a href="{{ paper.url }}" class="link">Read on E5 <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
    </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <p class="vc-record-colophon">Set in Cormorant Garamond &amp; Inter. Convened in {{ site.established.city }}. <em>For the next thousand years.</em></p>
</section>

<section class="vc-feat">
  <div class="vc-feat-rubric reveal">How The Record works</div>
  <h2 class="vc-feat-h reveal">Published openly. <em>Built to be cited.</em></h2>
  <div class="vc-feat-cols reveal">
    <div class="vc-feat-col">
      <h3><span class="roman">I.</span>Open Record</h3>
      <p class="drop">Every paper enters The Record with named authorship, a published methodology section, and a citation block. <em>What is measured cannot be dismissed.</em></p>
    </div>
    <div class="vc-feat-col">
      <h3><span class="roman">II.</span>Dual-source verification</h3>
      <p class="drop">Empirical claims carry dual-source verification where the evidence permits it. The methodology section names both sources and any unresolved <em>open questions</em>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="vc-feat-col">
      <h3><span class="roman">III.</span>Living documents</h3>
      <p class="drop">The Record updates. When evidence sharpens, when methodology improves, when an open question closes — the record reflects it, with named, dated revisions in the <em>changelog</em>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
